HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1550
By Camper
A RESOLUTION to commend Tania Humphrey for her exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this General Assembly is pleased to recognize
certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment
of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Tania Humphrey is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Representative Karen Camper; Ms. Humphrey's work has resulted
in innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole;
and
WHEREAS, a senior at Middle Tennessee State University, where she is highly
regarded by her peers, Ms. Humphrey is majoring in political science on a pre-law track with a
minor in journalism; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Tania Humphrey brought her many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, during her tenure as a legislative intern, she has risen to every challenge
presented to her, going above and beyond in the performance of her duties; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Humphrey has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight
and rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend Tania Humphrey for outstanding service as a
HJR1550
